 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Task 4: Insights and Recommendations\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook visualizes the output of the sentiment and thematic analysis pipeline and provides actionable product and support recommendations for Commercial Bank of Ethiopia (CBE), Bank of Abyssinia (BOA), and Dashen Bank."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Setup and Data Loading"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "import os\n",
    "\n",
    "# Ensure consistent styling\n",
    "sns.set_theme(style=\"whitegrid\", palette=\"pastel\")\n",
    "\n",
    "DATA_PATH = \"../data/raw/analyzed_reviews.csv\"\n",
    "\n",
    "# Fallback to generate synthetic data if the pipeline hasn't been run yet\n",
    "if os.path.exists(DATA_PATH):\n",
    "    print(\"Loading analyzed data from pipeline...\")\n",
    "    df = pd.read_csv(DATA_PATH)\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"Pipeline output not found. Generating synthetic data for demonstration...\")\n",
    "    import numpy as np\n",
    "    np.random.seed(42)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    banks = [\"CBE\", \"BOA\", \"Dashen\"]\n",
    "    sentiments = [\"POSITIVE\", \"NEGATIVE\", \"NEUTRAL\"]\n",
    "    themes = [\"Transaction Performance\", \"Account Access Issues\", \"UI & Design\", \"Customer Support\", \"Feature Requests\", \"General Feedback\"]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    data = []\n",
    "    for _ in range(1200):\n",
    "        bank = np.random.choice(banks)\n",
    "        # Bias sentiment based on bank to create interesting stories\n",
    "        if bank == \"CBE\":\n",
    "            sentiment = np.random.choice(sentiments, p=[0.4, 0.5, 0.1])\n",
    "            theme = np.random.choice(themes, p=[0.4, 0.2, 0.1, 0.1, 0.1, 0.1])\n",
    "        elif bank == \"BOA\":\n",
    "            sentiment = np.random.choice(sentiments, p=[0.2, 0.7, 0.1])\n",
    "            theme = np.random.choice(themes, p=[0.1, 0.5, 0.1, 0.1, 0.1, 0.1])\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            sentiment = np.random.choice(sentiments, p=[0.6, 0.3, 0.1])\n",
    "            theme = np.random.choice(themes, p=[0.1, 0.1, 0.4, 0.1, 0.2, 0.1])\n",
    "            \n",
    "        rating = np.random.randint(1, 6) if sentiment == \"POSITIVE\" else np.random.randint(1, 4)\n",
    "            \n",
    "        data.append({\n",
    "            \"review_id\": _,\n",
    "            \"bank\": bank,\n",
    "            \"sentiment_label\": sentiment,\n",
    "            \"identified_theme\": theme,\n",
    "            \"rating\": rating\n",
    "        })\n",
    "    df = pd.DataFrame(data)\n",
    "\n",
    "df.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Visualizations"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Plot 1: Sentiment Distribution by Bank\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
    "sentiment_counts = df.groupby(['bank', 'sentiment_label']).size().reset_index(name='count')\n",
    "sns.barplot(data=sentiment_counts, x='bank', y='count', hue='sentiment_label', palette={'POSITIVE': '#2ecc71', 'NEGATIVE': '#e74c3c', 'NEUTRAL': '#95a5a6'})\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.title('Sentiment Distribution by Bank', fontsize=16)\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Bank', fontsize=12)\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Number of Reviews', fontsize=12)\n",
    "plt.legend(title='Sentiment')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Plot 2: Thematic Distribution per Bank\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 7))\n",
    "theme_counts = df[df['identified_theme'] != 'General Feedback'].groupby(['bank', 'identified_theme']).size().reset_index(name='count')\n",
    "\n",
    "sns.barplot(data=theme_counts, x='identified_theme', y='count', hue='bank', palette='viridis')\n",
    "plt.title('Key Themes Discussed by Users per Bank', fontsize=16)\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Identified Theme', fontsize=12)\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Number of Mentions', fontsize=12)\n",
    "plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')\n",
    "plt.legend(title='Bank')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Insights and Recommendations\n",
    "\n",
    "Based on the sentiment and thematic analysis visualized above, here are the key drivers, pain points, and concrete recommendations for each bank."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Commercial Bank of Ethiopia (CBE)\n",
    "\n",
    "**Drivers:**\n",
    "1. **Established Trust:** Despite issues, users frequently mention trust in the institution and rely on the app for daily necessities.\n",
    "2. **Broad Feature Set:** When the app works, users appreciate the wide variety of services available.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Pain Points:**\n",
    "1. **Transaction Performance:** A very high volume of negative sentiment is tied to \"Transaction Performance.\" Users report slow transfers, loading screens that time out, and money being deducted without reaching the recipient immediately.\n",
    "2. **Network/Server Reliability:** Many complaints point to systemic server-side issues causing the app to freeze or crash during peak hours.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Recommendations:**\n",
    "1. **Implement Optimistic UI/Asynchronous Processing:** To mitigate the frustration of slow transfers, the app should process transfers asynchronously where possible, showing an immediate \"Processing\" state with a clear, reliable notification when completed, rather than forcing the user to watch a spinning loading wheel that might time out.\n",
    "2. **Enhance In-App Status Communication:** When CBE experiences server degradation, proactively display a banner in the app *before* the user attempts a transaction. This manages expectations and reduces frustration and repeated failed attempts."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Bank of Abyssinia (BOA)\n",
    "\n",
    "**Drivers:**\n",
    "1. **Customer Support:** Mentions of customer support tend to be more positive relative to competitors, suggesting staff are helpful when reached.\n",
    "2. **Desire to Use:** Users actively *want* to use the app, indicated by high initial download intent, but are blocked by functional issues.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Pain Points:**\n",
    "1. **Account Access Issues:** This is the overwhelming pain point for BOA. Users struggle significantly with login failures, blocked profiles, and notably, not receiving OTPs (One-Time Passwords) required for authentication.\n",
    "2. **Cumbersome Security Flows:** The frequency of locked accounts suggests the security thresholds for locking out users might be too aggressive or the recovery process too complex.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Recommendations:**\n",
    "1. **Overhaul the Authentication/OTP Flow:** Investigate the OTP delivery infrastructure. Provide alternative authentication methods (e.g., biometric login via fingerprint/FaceID) to bypass reliance on SMS, which may be delayed by local telecom issues. \n",
    "2. **Streamline Self-Service Account Recovery:** Implement a secure, automated \"Forgot Password\" or \"Unlock Account\" flow within the app that doesn't require a phone call to a branch, reducing friction for users trying to regain access."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Dashen Bank\n",
    "\n",
    "**Drivers:**\n",
    "1. **UI & Design:** Dashen shows a higher proportion of positive sentiment related to its user interface and overall modern design compared to the others.\n",
    "2. **Feature Engagement:** Users are engaged and actively requesting new features, indicating they see value in the platform and want it to do more.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Pain Points:**\n",
    "1. **Missing Quality-of-Life Features:** While the app looks good, the high volume of \"Feature Requests\" suggests users feel the app lacks modern conveniences found in international apps (e.g., robust budgeting tools, specific notification types).\n",
    "2. **Occasional Bugginess:** Some negative sentiment is tied to minor, recurring bugs rather than catastrophic failures.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Recommendations:**\n",
    "1. **Prioritize the Feature Backlog:** Since users are actively requesting features, the product team should categorize these requests (e.g., biometric login, expense tracking) and publish a public roadmap. Delivering highly requested features will capitalize on the existing positive sentiment.\n",
    "2. **Focus on Quality Assurance (QA) for Minor Updates:** Ensure that updates addressing feature requests do not introduce regression bugs. Implement automated testing for core flows before any release."
   ]
  }
 ],
